<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 1:44PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHWESTERN RANDOLPH...CENTRAL
UPSHUR AND SOUTH CENTRAL BARBOUR COUNTIES THROUGH 215 PM EDT...
At 144 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Rock Cave, or 10 miles south of Buckhannon, moving
northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Elkins, Belington, Beverly, Junior, Womelsdorf (Coalton), Alexander,
Ellamore, Tallmansville, and Alton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
